The paper deals with metric decompositions of graphs, which is a topic in both computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The notion of path-separable graphs is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and the paper uses probabilistic techniques, which are often used in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
